main event: Two connected, rectangular objects with bluish-white lights were spotted moving in the sky over Tillamook, Oregon in 1960.
interesting points: The objects were observed by an experienced and qualified air traffic control tower operator at the Portland International Airport.
The objects moved at an estimated speed of 1,502 mph.
Multiple witnesses, including a civilian observer and a flight line sentry, reported seeing bright moving lights in the sky.
There was no known air traffic or balloon releases that could account for the sightings.
The weather conditions were clear with no unusual meteorological or astronomical activity that could explain the sightings.
sighted object: two connected, rectangular objects with bluish-white lights
witnesses: air traffic control tower operator, civilian observer, flight line sentry
